1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,300
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,540
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:15,900
Mr. Seo.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Team Manager Ko.

5
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:22,700
How come you're here?

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,633
I'm here on behalf of the Chairman.

7
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,000
(Episode 36)

8
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:32,233
You should greet your father first.

9
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:33,733
Yes.

10
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:36,400
I'll wait outside,

11
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,200
so take your time and talk to him.

12
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:39,900
Yes.

13
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,833
(Late Han Su Cheol)

14
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,300
I'm here, Dad.

15
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:54,433
I'm sorry I didn't come see you
as soon as I returned.

16
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:00,533
How are you doing there?

17
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:14,800
While designing the retirement community,
I thought of you a lot.

18
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:20,233
What kind of home would you have built?

19
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,300
If you saw the house I designed,

20
00:01:26,933 --> 00:01:28,200
what would you say?

21
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:33,900
This morning,

22
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:37,400
Grandma asked me
to have my birthday meal with her,

23
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,000
but I couldn't.

24
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,500
It might be my last birthday...

25
00:01:47,633 --> 00:01:49,100
spending time with Grandpa, and yet I...

26
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:53,933
I'm such a terrible person, aren't I?

27
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:56,033
(Late Han Su Cheol)

28
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,500
But you know,

29
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,300
I hate my birthday.

30
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:06,800
If it hadn't been
for my birthday party that day, you...

31
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:13,900
I miss you.

32
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,400
Dad.

33
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,200
Mr. Seo.

34
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:37,500
So, did you have a good talk
with your father?

35
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,233
Yes. I came early in the morning
on purpose...

36
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:41,700
so Grandpa wouldn't worry.

37
00:02:42,233 --> 00:02:44,200
Thank you for coming.

38
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,100
You never even met my dad.

39
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,300
You're heading to the office, right?

40
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:51,333
Yes. What about you?

41
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,400
I should go to the office too.
How did you get here?

42
00:02:54,533 --> 00:02:57,100
I took the bus. What about you?

43
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,833
Same here. Shall we go?

44
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:03,233
By the way, why don't you drive?

45
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:05,300
I have severe vision issues.

46
00:03:05,733 --> 00:03:08,000
I do have a license,
but I just don't drive.

47
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:09,333
I see.

48
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,600
Why don't you drive?

49
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,933
I don't even have a license.

50
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,200
We should get going.

51
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,200
The bus will be leaving soon. Let's go.

52
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:25,533
Seriously.

53
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,100
Showing up on your first day
with a cast on...

54
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,933
And you're supposed
to start driving right away.

55
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:34,833
I'm sorry.
They said it'll be fine in about a week,

56
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,300
so please understand.

57
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:39,500
Hey, Seong Jun.

58
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,300
Since it's your first time working
in the secretary's office,

59
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,933
you probably don't know this,

60
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,400
but an executive assistant
can't just fall sick whenever they want.

61
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:48,700
If you're sick,

62
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:51,300
it messes up my entire business
as the CEO.

63
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,200
Do you understand what I'm saying?

64
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:57,800
Hey, why aren't you answering?

65
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:02,700
The basic rule for an assistant
is immediate response.

66
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,800
Sir, this is the office.

67
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:10,100
People are watching,
so please mind your form of address.

68
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,200
Form of address?

69
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:15,133
Right, got it. I'll be careful, Mr. Cho.

70
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:16,733
I'll get going now.

71
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:18,633
Wait.

72
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,733
So, this weekend, I was thinking...

73
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:23,900
we could have dinner at my place
with Gwon Sik and his wife.

74
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:26,100
A couples' dinner.

75
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,900
A couples' dinner?

76
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:31,800
Now that we're all part
of Kangsu Construction,

77
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,300
I thought we could all get together...

78
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:35,900
and get to know each other openly.
Are you okay with that?

79
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,100
I get your point, but it doesn't have
to be a couples' gathering.

80
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:43,700
Seriously!
I'm the CEO, and you're the assistant.

81
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:46,400
An assistant just does
what the CEO tells them to do...

82
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,233
and follows decisions, no questions asked.

83
00:04:49,933 --> 00:04:51,700
- What is it?
- Glad you are here.

84
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:54,000
Mr. Cho, if you're done, come see me.

85
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,400
Wait, Yong Man. You're taking Seong Jun...

86
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:59,433
Why do you need Mr. Cho?

87
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,600
What do you mean, why? As a senior,

88
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,233
there's plenty I need to teach my junior.

89
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:06,133
What could you possibly teach
when you don't know anything yourself?

90
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,133
No, please teach me well.

91
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,500
You heard him, right?

92
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:15,600
As expected, you're something else.

93
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Follow me.

94
00:05:21,933 --> 00:05:25,433
What the? Are the current
and former assistants teaming up...

95
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:27,500
to leave me out?

96
00:05:30,033 --> 00:05:32,500
By the way, why did Manager Seo
say we shouldn't throw...

97
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,700
a surprise party for the Team Manager?

98
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:36,700
I know. She always throws...

99
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:38,800
surprise parties for our birthdays.

100
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:42,100
What could it be? Is there some reason...

101
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,500
we shouldn't celebrate his birthday?

102
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:48,200
You said your dad was throwing you
a birthday party that day.

103
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,533
Did it go well?

104
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:53,000
Yes, it did.

105
00:05:57,433 --> 00:05:59,100
(Team Manager Ko Gyeol)

106
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,700
(Guide to Ko Dae Chi, by Ju Yong Man)

107
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,933
What is this?

108
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:12,700
Let me tell you,
I know CEO Ko better than anyone.

109
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:15,800
This contains detailed notes...

110
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,400
on how to handle... No, support him.

111
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,200
It'll be a big help.

112
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,533
Really?

113
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:31,400
Guide to Ko Dae Chi, by Ju Yong Man.

114
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:34,033
Chapter one,
records of Ko Dae Chi's reactions.

115
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,433
One, basic specs of Ko Dae Chi.

116
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,700
Two, early warning signs
when Dae Chi gets angry.

117
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:43,500
You know how CEO Ko is. He snaps easily.

118
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:46,733
When that happens,
just ignore it like a barking dog.

119
00:06:47,133 --> 00:06:49,600
But if it's something
you really can't stand,

120
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:51,900
mutter it under your breath.

121
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,600
He somehow hears those things well.

122
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,100
For more details, refer to the notes.

123
00:06:58,100 --> 00:06:59,100
Yes.

124
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:04,400
No matter what, the most important virtue
of an assistant...

125
00:07:05,433 --> 00:07:06,533
is being tight-lipped.

126
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:09,633
Lock it up tight.

127
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:15,200
Mr. Seo is the expert at that.
Where did he go?

128
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,700
(Team Manager Ko Gyeol)

129
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:29,233
Team Manager, are you coming in now?

130
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:30,933
Yes.

131
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:34,300
Happy birthday.
You should've told me yesterday.

132
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,300
Apparently, it's the company tradition
to send flowers on birthdays.

133
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:49,300
What's wrong? Did something happen?

134
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,700
No, it's nothing.

135
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,633
If you don't like flowers,
should I move them to the pantry?

136
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:58,133
Could you? I'm allergic to flowers.

137
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,633
I see.

138
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,400
Hello, Mr. Ju.

139
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:09,700
I went there in the morning.
Yes, thank you.

140
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,933
Looks like you went somewhere.

141
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:15,700
Did you have seaweed soup this morning?

142
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:19,533
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
could you organize and send me...

143
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:21,100
the second-round software materials
by tomorrow?

144
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,533
Yes, Team Manager.

145
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:43,200
You're going to sign the contract
dressed like that?

146
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:45,600
Yes, I thought today should be special,

147
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,100
so I put in some effort. How do I look?

148
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,400
Seriously? You don't look like an artist,
more like a club regular.

149
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,800
Did you pierce your ears?

150
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:57,300
Why is a man wearing earrings
and a necklace?

151
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,600
I guess you're no different, Mom.

152
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,600
This symbolizes a creator's free will...

153
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:07,000
Forget it. Where are you going?

154
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,233
There's a memorial service
at the Chairman's, so I'm going to help.

155
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:10,233
Why are you going there?

156
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:13,233
The maid and the two madams are there.

157
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:15,500
One of them doesn't count.

158
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:19,300
She doesn't help. She just causes trouble.

159
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Right, she's like that.

160
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:25,100
Anyway, don't get overexcited.
Just behave.

161
00:09:25,633 --> 00:09:28,600
And don't let that web novelist
intimidate you. Be confident.

162
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:30,100
Yes, sir.

163
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:32,600
I'll load this into the car for you.

164
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,433
Want me to give you a ride
to your meeting?

165
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:36,033
Mom, you've got great instincts.

166
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:46,300
(Cho Eun Nim, Seo Seung Wu)

167
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:50,800
I can't believe it.

168
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,233
I can't believe that my name
now has "artist" attached to it,

169
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:55,600
and that I get to make a living
from my drawings.

170
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:57,800
This is a huge honor for my family.

171
00:09:58,233 --> 00:10:01,233
Take it down a notch.
It's not that big a deal.

172
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:02,600
It is a big deal.

173
00:10:03,433 --> 00:10:06,900
I'm seriously holding myself back...

174
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:10,000
from buying everyone in this café
a drink right now.

175
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:12,700
My mom told me not to get ahead of myself.

176
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,700
The contract has been finalized.

177
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:16,600
- Let me take a quick call.
- Okay.

178
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:24,500
So your real name is Cho Eun Nim.

179
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,500
Let me properly introduce myself.

180
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:33,200
My name is Seo Seung Wu.

181
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:38,000
Didn't ask, don't care.

182
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,400
Right, you didn't ask and don't care,

183
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:45,700
but we're partners now,

184
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,633
so you should at least know my name.

185
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,633
More importantly...

186
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,000
How much do you get paid per episode?

187
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:55,500
I'm sure it's a lot more than me.

188
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,800
- Hey.
- I mean,

189
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,500
what does the fee matter?

190
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:05,133
Anyway, how will we proceed
with our work going forward?

191
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:08,600
Will we co-write drafts together, or...

192
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,533
Right, I was so desperate for a contract,

193
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:19,233
I forgot you were a crazy girl.

194
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,000
Let's stay calm.

195
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,600
- What? A studio?
- What? A studio?

196
00:11:28,633 --> 00:11:31,100
Yes. Since this is a joint project,

197
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:32,800
if you work separately,

198
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,733
communication might be difficult.

199
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,533
But meeting outside every time...

200
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:39,100
would also be inefficient.

201
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,000
So we've decided...

202
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,400
to provide you with a studio.

203
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:46,800
A studio? Is this a dream or reality?

204
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:47,800
I'll pass.

205
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:51,200
I'll just keep working in my own room.

206
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,900
If it were anyone else...

207
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,900
How could I possibly work with him?

208
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:58,233
Come on, what?

209
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,900
What kind of person do you think I am?

210
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:05,500
From now on, we're on the same boat.
We're comrades.

211
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:09,600
Exactly. Shall we get up?
You should take a look at the studio.

212
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:11,800
Yes, Producer!

213
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:23,600
We could just do it ourselves.
You didn't have to help.

214
00:12:24,033 --> 00:12:25,733
I should help out too.

215
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:28,333
You're getting older, Madam.

216
00:12:28,533 --> 00:12:30,400
You shouldn't be working
in the kitchen anymore.

217
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,233
It's something I've done my whole life,
so it's not hard for me.

218
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,100
Don't worry.

219
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:39,700
Gyeol is really lucky
to have grandparents like you.

220
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:43,500
What kind of family would do this
for an adopted grandchild?

221
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:49,500
I'm sorry, ma'am. I misspoke.

222
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:53,600
Gyeol is no different
from my own grandson.

223
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,900
From now on,
don't say anything like that again.

224
00:12:58,433 --> 00:12:59,500
Yes, ma'am.

225
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:03,300
By the way, is Su Jeong not home?

226
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:05,000
She's been busy lately.

227
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:08,200
She's studying French or whatever.

228
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:09,700
Studying French?

229
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,500
Bonjour, mademoiselle. Bonjour, monsieur.

230
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:15,233
Bonjour, madame.

231
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:18,833
Why? Are you trying to get back
at Kang Yeon Ja?

232
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,200
Get back at her? No, I...

233
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:25,700
Yes, you majored in French literature.

234
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,500
Mother, these days,

235
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,700
you can just order memorial food
and have it delivered,

236
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,700
so why go to all this trouble?

237
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:36,900
You're holding a memorial
for someone you don't even know.

238
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:38,800
Watch it.

239
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,800
Hello.

240
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,800
- You're here?
- Yes.

241
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,900
You're working hard, Jeong Ran.

242
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:46,833
Not at all.

243
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:51,200
Memorial food is all about sincerity.
Like this.

244
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:55,033
Should I help out a bit, Yeong Hwa?

245
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,533
Bring out the chestnuts
so I can peel them.

246
00:13:58,033 --> 00:14:00,200
It's almost done. Please go inside.

247
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:03,000
Or maybe take a walk in the garden.

248
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:06,000
Father,
would you like to take a walk with me?

249
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,700
No, you just keep frying the pancakes.

250
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,600
Right, what was I thinking?

251
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:19,533
I have a screen golf appointment today.
Bien joué!

252
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:24,300
It means, "Nice, nice shot!"

253
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,700
I'm going to be late.

254
00:14:28,133 --> 00:14:29,633
She's really something.

255
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:33,500
It's not easy to stay that consistent.

256
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:38,233
Su Jeong is a star
even at our dance class.

257
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:41,900
Why? Did she make a scene there too?

258
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,933
Actually,
she keeps clashing with one member,

259
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,400
but that lady is no pushover either,

260
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,400
so Su Jeong ends up losing every time.

261
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:55,300
It's rare for her to be bested by anyone.

262
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:57,200
I'm curious who it is.

263
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:00,300
(Complete Collection
of Past CSAT Math Questions)

264
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:03,033
Yes, the room is in great condition.

265
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:05,933
It has a bed, desk, and wardrobe,

266
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:08,600
all the basic furniture,
so you can just move right in.

267
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,000
Please come take a look.

268
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:15,300
I hope the room gets rented soon.

269
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:20,200
What's that posted outside?

270
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,000
I put Eun Ae's room up for rent.

271
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,433
It's to earn even a little more
for living expenses.

272
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:30,700
Eun Nim and Eun Ae can just share
a room again like before.

273
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:32,800
Do you really have to go that far?

274
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:36,033
Eun Hyeong's dad got rehired
at a major company.

275
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:39,000
At our age,
we don't know what might happen,

276
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,433
so we have to make money
while we still can.

277
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,800
Thinking about how
I was so clueless before...

278
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:49,433
and thought I was done
with my responsibilities...

279
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:53,533
By the way,
Eun Hyeong's dad is quite something.

280
00:15:53,933 --> 00:15:57,100
How did he get rehired
at a major company so quickly?

281
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,833
Quickly? While working as a cleaner,

282
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:02,900
he secretly went to countless interviews.

283
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:07,300
I'm just so relieved
he finally got such a good job.

284
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,600
You really are like yourself now.

285
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:13,300
That determined look on your face,

286
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:14,900
it's like you're back to your old self.

287
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,400
Yes, you know...

288
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,500
I'm going to work harder in real estate,

289
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:22,000
and I've started studying again.

290
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,333
Studying? Again? What kind of studying?

291
00:16:24,533 --> 00:16:27,033
I'm going to go to college.

292
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:30,900
You mean...

293
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,133
you're going to prepare
for the college entrance exam...

294
00:16:33,133 --> 00:16:35,633
like kids in their twenties?

295
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:38,600
Yes. Even if I can't make it this year,

296
00:16:38,933 --> 00:16:40,300
I'll definitely get in within a few years.

297
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:44,700
That's right.
Once you set your mind to something,

298
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:47,033
you see it through completely.

299
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:51,300
I wish Cho Rong...

300
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:53,200
had that kind of drive too.

301
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:57,000
Cho Rong doesn't seem ordinary these days.

302
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,600
I told her to stop doing useless things...

303
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:01,533
and either go to college...

304
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:04,733
or learn a skill and become independent.

305
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:08,033
She never listens,

306
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:10,000
it's driving me crazy.

307
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,400
Mala, once you succeed,

308
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,933
our restaurant's new trio menu
will be born.

309
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,500
Be delicious.

310
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,233
Hot!

311
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:32,533
Spicy!

312
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,400
So spicy!

313
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,300
It's already time to get off work.

314
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:45,200
Eun Ae, are you heading out too?

315
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:47,833
Me? I'll stay a bit longer.

316
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,100
You all go ahead.

317
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,700
- See you tomorrow.
- See you tomorrow.

318
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,700
See you... Tomorrow.

319
00:18:03,533 --> 00:18:04,933
What's this?

320
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:07,700
You know what my birthday means to me.

321
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,600
Who said this was a birthday gift?

322
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,933
You were really cool at the presentation.

323
00:18:15,633 --> 00:18:16,633
How should I put it?

324
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:20,033
It felt like you'd gone back
to your childhood self.

325
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,300
Open it and see.

326
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:44,933
When you design,
you start by sketching by hand.

327
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,433
I even had your name engraved
on the ruler.

328
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:52,800
You didn't have to.
I could've bought one myself.

329
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,000
He wasn't in the office. Where did he go?

330
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:05,000
I thought about what kind of comfort
I could give you today,

331
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,900
how I could ease your burden,

332
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:10,500
but I couldn't figure it out.

333
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:15,533
So I just prepared this
to show my support and encouragement.

334
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,133
Please accept it
without feeling pressured.

335
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:21,733
Thank you. I'll use it well.

336
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:30,000
Team Manager Ko doesn't like cake,
so you didn't have to go to the trouble.

337
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:33,200
I didn't know he didn't like cake.

338
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,233
I'll get going now.

339
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:50,800
Happy birthday
to the most noble team manager!

340
00:19:55,033 --> 00:19:57,833
Manager Seo always takes good care
of things anyway.

341
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,600
What should I do with the cake?

342
00:20:02,133 --> 00:20:03,633
Someone will eat it tomorrow.

343
00:20:35,133 --> 00:20:36,133
Manager Han.

344
00:20:37,233 --> 00:20:40,300
This will probably be the last memorial...

345
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:42,200
held in this house.

346
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:45,933
I'll be going to where you are soon.

347
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:51,300
I don't know if I'll be able
to face you confidently there.

348
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,000
I tried to raise him well,

349
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,400
even if not as well as you would have,

350
00:20:58,033 --> 00:21:01,633
but it wasn't as easy as I thought.

351
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,400
With the little time I have left,

352
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:08,933
my wish is
to see him firmly settle down...

353
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:10,833
before I go.

354
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,300
Please help.

355
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,100
Come and offer a drink.

356
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:26,100
Me?

357
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:31,000
You've spent so many years
with Manager Han. Come on.

358
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:35,300
No, I mean, even so...

359
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,400
Father is really something.

360
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:49,900
Why ask Dae Chi to offer the drink?

361
00:21:50,133 --> 00:21:51,133
Mother.

362
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,733
Since this will be the last year...

363
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:15,200
we can hold this memorial,

364
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,000
I asked everyone to gather.

365
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:21,000
Come on, Father.

366
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,000
Miracles do happen.

367
00:22:24,533 --> 00:22:26,633
You should still be here with us next year
and the year after,

368
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:28,433
just like this.

369
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:31,733
Do you think things go the way we want?

370
00:22:34,133 --> 00:22:38,400
I know my time is coming.

371
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,133
CEO Ko.

372
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,933
Even if you stop holding memorials
from next year,

373
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:49,700
make sure to visit the columbarium
with Gyeol...

374
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:51,933
in my place.

375
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,900
Me? Visit the columbarium?

376
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:58,400
Please do that.

377
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:02,200
I heard you went early this morning...

378
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:05,300
to see your father alone.

379
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:08,500
Yes. Mr. Seo was already there,

380
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:09,733
so we came back together.

381
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,400
Mr. Seo went there?

382
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:16,400
I used to go with you every year,

383
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:19,400
but since you couldn't this year,
I quietly went by myself.

384
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:23,600
Well done. Thank you.

385
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:26,000
Manager Han...

386
00:23:26,733 --> 00:23:29,500
must have accumulated a lot of good karma.

387
00:23:30,833 --> 00:23:32,400
Gyeol, did you see?

388
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,600
All these strong pillars...

389
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,233
are standing by your side to support you.

390
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,900
Yes, thank you all so much.

391
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:46,200
From what I saw in this competition,
both of you did your part well.

392
00:23:48,033 --> 00:23:49,900
If you two continue to work well together,

393
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,833
the future of Kangsu Construction
will be very bright.

394
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,033
I'll keep that in mind, Grandpa.

395
00:23:57,733 --> 00:24:00,500
If I lead from the front
and my two sons push from behind,

396
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:02,633
Kangsu Group will be unstoppable.

397
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,433
That's right.

398
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:13,700
Why did you go there?
It's not like Father asked you to.

399
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,900
I told you.
I used to go with the Chairman every year,

400
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,133
but since he couldn't this year,
I went alone.

401
00:24:19,333 --> 00:24:20,933
You both were out here?

402
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:23,200
Yes.

403
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:25,400
Why did you come out?

404
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,400
I left something at the office.

405
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,400
So you're going there at this hour?

406
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,433
I'll be right back.

407
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,633
Mr. Seo, thank you for today.

408
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,900
- All right, go ahead.
- Yes.

409
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,000
See you.

410
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:45,600
I'll get going too.

411
00:24:46,233 --> 00:24:47,233
Seo Gwon Sik.

412
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:52,200
I'm warning you. Don't act rashly.

413
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,233
(Happy birthday
to the most noble team manager!)

414
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,633
(Happy birthday
to the most noble team manager!)

415
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,633
Joy, come to think of it,

416
00:26:00,633 --> 00:26:03,300
I don't think I know anything
about the Team Manager.

417
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:06,233
Mom, you know...

418
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:08,433
what he was like at seven, brave and cool.

419
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,700
Maybe too much time has passed.

420
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:14,100
Back then,
he seemed so excited about his birthday,

421
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:16,900
but today he looked kind of upset...

422
00:26:18,133 --> 00:26:20,733
No, more like sad.

423
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:24,533
I still wanted
to congratulate him sincerely.

424
00:26:28,100 --> 00:26:30,700
Another video call? What should I do?

425
00:26:34,633 --> 00:26:35,633
Hello?

426
00:26:35,933 --> 00:26:37,133
Why did you just leave?

427
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:41,700
I thought you bought this
to celebrate my birthday.

428
00:26:42,533 --> 00:26:43,933
Well, yes, but...

429
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:48,000
You didn't seem to be
in a good mood all day, and...

430
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:52,100
I wasn't earlier, but I'm fine now.

431
00:26:52,733 --> 00:26:54,900
I felt better
the moment I saw this lion cake.

432
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:58,533
Really? Then it's not past midnight yet,

433
00:26:58,533 --> 00:27:00,300
so should we celebrate
your birthday together now?

434
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:03,600
What? How would we celebrate together?

435
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:06,500
If you light the candles, I could sing...

436
00:27:09,033 --> 00:27:10,600
Do you not like that kind of thing?

437
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:15,600
No,
let's light the candles together and sing.

438
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:17,500
And let's blow them out together.

439
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,400
I'm lighting the candles.

440
00:27:36,333 --> 00:27:37,333
They're lit.

441
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:44,233
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

442
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:50,333
<i>Happy birthday, dear Team Manager
Happy birthday to you</i>

443
00:27:53,533 --> 00:27:55,500
Shall we blow out
the candles together now?

444
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:57,933
Wait, you should make a wish.

445
00:27:58,800 --> 00:27:59,800
A wish?

446
00:28:11,233 --> 00:28:12,300
Now let's blow them out together.

447
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:27,833
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
